        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Erik Meijer'); ?>
        <?php echo $this->stencil->addHeadshot('Erik Meijer', 'jpg', 'left'); ?>
        <p><strong>Erik Meijer</strong> is a Dutch computer scientist and entrepreneur. From 2000 to early 2013 he was a software architect for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?> where he headed the Cloud Programmability Team. He then founded Applied Duality Inc in 2013. Before that, he was an associate professor at Utrecht University.</p>
        <p>Meijer's research has included the areas of functional programming (particularly <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Haskell', 'L'); ?>) compiler implementation, parsing, programming language design, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('XML', 'WD'); ?>, and foreign function interfaces.</p>
        <p>His work at Microsoft included <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C#', 'LC'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Visual Basic', 'LB'); ?>, LINQ, Volta, and the Reactive programming framework (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Reactive Extensions', 'IT'); ?>) for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('.Net', 'L'); ?>.</p>
        <p>In 2009, he was the recipient of the Microsoft Outstanding Technical Leadership Award and in 2007 the Outstanding Technical Achievement Award as a member of the C# team.</p>
        <p>In 2011 Erik was appointed part-time professor of Cloud Programming within the Software Engineering Research Group at Delft University of Technology. He is also member of the ACM Queue Editorial Board.</p>
        <p>Date of birth: 18 April 1963</p>
